        "documentation": {
          "referenceAndScope": "Assembly of one research GPS enclosure in Switzerland in 2025. The activity includes PETG 3D printing, electricity used for printing, installation of the GPS tracker and galvanised screws and nuts, and generation of plastic printing waste. Upstream production of linked components and end-of-life treatment of the assembled box are outside this foreground activity.",
          "functionalUnit": "",
          "pasAssumptions": "",
          "balancedEquation": "",
          "calculationNotes": "Component masses are based on the project bill of materials and weighing records. PETG and plastic waste amounts are based on the 3D-printing record; electricity is calculated from printer power and operating time. Linked GPS tracker and screw quantities are taken from the corresponding foreground activities. ecoinvent datasets are used as documented proxies for background inputs.",
          "explanationLines": []
        },
