            "scaledUnit": "kg",
            "description": "estimated through the below online references ",
            "reference": "Source: https://galvanizeit.org/design-and-fabrication/design-considerations/weight-increase\n\nThe total mass of galvanized screws was reported as 0.0149 kg. The zinc coating mass was estimated using galvanization weight-gain data reported by the American Galvanizers Association. For lightweight steel components with high surface-area-to-mass ratios (“light truss”), galvanization increases the mass of the original steel by 2.60–6.08%. The mean value (4.34%) was adopted. Assuming the reported screw mass corresponds to the final galvanized fasteners, the screws were modelled as 0.01428 kg unalloyed steel and 0.00062 kg zinc coating.",
